44// Maximum number of channels for which the capture channel data is stored on
45// the stack. If the number of channels are larger than this, they are stored
46// using scratch memory that is pre-allocated on the heap. The reason for this
47// partitioning is not to waste heap space for handling the more common numbers
48// of channels, while at the same time not limiting the support for higher
49// numbers of channels by enforcing the capture channel data to be stored on the
50// stack using a fixed maximum value.
51constexpr size_t kMaxNumChannelsOnStack = 2;
52
53// Chooses the number of channels to store on the heap when that is required due
54// to the number of capture channels being larger than the pre-defined number
55// of channels to store on the stack.
56size_t NumChannelsOnHeap(size_t num_capture_channels) {
57 return num_capture_channels > kMaxNumChannelsOnStack ? num_capture_channels
58 : 0;
59}
60
61void LinearEchoPower(const FftData& E,
62 const FftData& Y,
63 std::array<float, kFftLengthBy2Plus1>* S2) {
64 for (size_t k = 0; k < E.re.size(); ++k) {
65 (*S2)[k] = (Y.re[k] - E.re[k]) * (Y.re[k] - E.re[k]) +
66 (Y.im[k] - E.im[k]) * (Y.im[k] - E.im[k]);
67 }
68}
69
70// Fades between two input signals using a fix-sized transition.
71void SignalTransition(rtc::ArrayView<const float> from,
72 rtc::ArrayView<const float> to,
73 rtc::ArrayView<float> out) {
74 if (from == to) {
75 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(to.size(), out.size());
76 std::copy(to.begin(), to.end(), out.begin());
77 } else {
78 constexpr size_t kTransitionSize = 30;
79 constexpr float kOneByTransitionSizePlusOne = 1.f / (kTransitionSize + 1);
80
81 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(from.size(), to.size());
82 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(from.size(), out.size());
83 RTC_DCHECK_LE(kTransitionSize, out.size());
84
85 for (size_t k = 0; k < kTransitionSize; ++k) {
86 float a = (k + 1) * kOneByTransitionSizePlusOne;
87 out[k] = a * to[k] + (1.f - a) * from[k];
88 }
89
90 std::copy(to.begin() + kTransitionSize, to.end(),
91 out.begin() + kTransitionSize);
92 }
93}
94
95// Computes a windowed (square root Hanning) padded FFT and updates the related
96// memory.
97void WindowedPaddedFft(const Aec3Fft& fft,
98 rtc::ArrayView<const float> v,
99 rtc::ArrayView<float> v_old,
100 FftData* V) {
101 fft.PaddedFft(v, v_old, Aec3Fft::Window::kSqrtHanning, V);
102 std::copy(v.begin(), v.end(), v_old.begin());
103}

105// Class for removing the echo from the capture signal.
106class EchoRemoverImpl final : public EchoRemover {
107 public:
108 EchoRemoverImpl(const EchoCanceller3Config& config,
109 int sample_rate_hz,
110 size_t num_render_channels,
111 size_t num_capture_channels);
112 ~EchoRemoverImpl() override;
113 EchoRemoverImpl(const EchoRemoverImpl&) = delete;
114 EchoRemoverImpl& operator=(const EchoRemoverImpl&) = delete;
115
116 void GetMetrics(EchoControl::Metrics* metrics) const override;
117
118 // Removes the echo from a block of samples from the capture signal. The
119 // supplied render signal is assumed to be pre-aligned with the capture
120 // signal.
121 void ProcessCapture(
122 EchoPathVariability echo_path_variability,
123 bool capture_signal_saturation,
124 const absl::optional<DelayEstimate>& external_delay,
125 RenderBuffer* render_buffer,
126 std::vector<std::vector<std::vector<float>>>* linear_output,
127 std::vector<std::vector<std::vector<float>>>* capture) override;
128
129 // Updates the status on whether echo leakage is detected in the output of the
130 // echo remover.
131 void UpdateEchoLeakageStatus(bool leakage_detected) override {
132 echo_leakage_detected_ = leakage_detected;
133 }
134
135 void SetCaptureOutputUsage(bool capture_output_used) override {
136 capture_output_used_ = capture_output_used;
137 }
138
139 private:
140 // Selects which of the coarse and refined linear filter outputs that is most
141 // appropriate to pass to the suppressor and forms the linear filter output by
142 // smoothly transition between those.
143 void FormLinearFilterOutput(const SubtractorOutput& subtractor_output,
144 rtc::ArrayView<float> output);
145
146 static int instance_count_;
147 const EchoCanceller3Config config_;
148 const Aec3Fft fft_;
149 std::unique_ptr<ApmDataDumper> data_dumper_;
150 const Aec3Optimization optimization_;
151 const int sample_rate_hz_;
152 const size_t num_render_channels_;
153 const size_t num_capture_channels_;
154 const bool use_coarse_filter_output_;
155 Subtractor subtractor_;
156 SuppressionGain suppression_gain_;
157 ComfortNoiseGenerator cng_;
158 SuppressionFilter suppression_filter_;
159 RenderSignalAnalyzer render_signal_analyzer_;
160 ResidualEchoEstimator residual_echo_estimator_;
161 bool echo_leakage_detected_ = false;
162 bool capture_output_used_ = true;
163 AecState aec_state_;
164 EchoRemoverMetrics metrics_;
165 std::vector<std::array<float, kFftLengthBy2>> e_old_;
166 std::vector<std::array<float, kFftLengthBy2>> y_old_;
167 size_t block_counter_ = 0;
168 int gain_change_hangover_ = 0;
169 bool refined_filter_output_last_selected_ = true;
170
171 std::vector<std::array<float, kFftLengthBy2>> e_heap_;
172 std::vector<std::array<float, kFftLengthBy2Plus1>> Y2_heap_;
173 std::vector<std::array<float, kFftLengthBy2Plus1>> E2_heap_;
174 std::vector<std::array<float, kFftLengthBy2Plus1>> R2_heap_;
175 std::vector<std::array<float, kFftLengthBy2Plus1>> S2_linear_heap_;
176 std::vector<FftData> Y_heap_;
177 std::vector<FftData> E_heap_;
178 std::vector<FftData> comfort_noise_heap_;
179 std::vector<FftData> high_band_comfort_noise_heap_;
180 std::vector<SubtractorOutput> subtractor_output_heap_;
181};

183int EchoRemoverImpl::instance_count_ = 0;

185EchoRemoverImpl::EchoRemoverImpl(const EchoCanceller3Config& config,
186 int sample_rate_hz,
187 size_t num_render_channels,
188 size_t num_capture_channels)
189 : config_(config),
190 fft_(),
191 data_dumper_(
192 new ApmDataDumper(rtc::AtomicOps::Increment(&instance_count_))),
193 optimization_(DetectOptimization()),
194 sample_rate_hz_(sample_rate_hz),
195 num_render_channels_(num_render_channels),
196 num_capture_channels_(num_capture_channels),
197 use_coarse_filter_output_(
198 config_.filter.enable_coarse_filter_output_usage),
199 subtractor_(config,
200 num_render_channels_,
201 num_capture_channels_,
202 data_dumper_.get(),
203 optimization_),
204 suppression_gain_(config_,
205 optimization_,
206 sample_rate_hz,
207 num_capture_channels),
208 cng_(config_, optimization_, num_capture_channels_),
209 suppression_filter_(optimization_,
210 sample_rate_hz_,
211 num_capture_channels_),
212 render_signal_analyzer_(config_),
213 residual_echo_estimator_(config_, num_render_channels),
214 aec_state_(config_, num_capture_channels_),
215 e_old_(num_capture_channels_, {0.f}),
216 y_old_(num_capture_channels_, {0.f}),
217 e_heap_(NumChannelsOnHeap(num_capture_channels_), {0.f}),
218 Y2_heap_(NumChannelsOnHeap(num_capture_channels_)),
219 E2_heap_(NumChannelsOnHeap(num_capture_channels_)),
220 R2_heap_(NumChannelsOnHeap(num_capture_channels_)),
221 S2_linear_heap_(NumChannelsOnHeap(num_capture_channels_)),
222 Y_heap_(NumChannelsOnHeap(num_capture_channels_)),
223 E_heap_(NumChannelsOnHeap(num_capture_channels_)),
224 comfort_noise_heap_(NumChannelsOnHeap(num_capture_channels_)),
225 high_band_comfort_noise_heap_(NumChannelsOnHeap(num_capture_channels_)),
226 subtractor_output_heap_(NumChannelsOnHeap(num_capture_channels_)) {
227 RTC_DCHECK(ValidFullBandRate(sample_rate_hz));
228}

230EchoRemoverImpl::~EchoRemoverImpl() = default;

232void EchoRemoverImpl::GetMetrics(EchoControl::Metrics* metrics) const {
233 // Echo return loss (ERL) is inverted to go from gain to attenuation.
234 metrics->echo_return_loss = -10.0 * std::log10(aec_state_.ErlTimeDomain());
235 metrics->echo_return_loss_enhancement =
236 Log2TodB(aec_state_.FullBandErleLog2());
237}
238
239void EchoRemoverImpl::ProcessCapture(
240 EchoPathVariability echo_path_variability,
241 bool capture_signal_saturation,
242 const absl::optional<DelayEstimate>& external_delay,
243 RenderBuffer* render_buffer,
244 std::vector<std::vector<std::vector<float>>>* linear_output,
245 std::vector<std::vector<std::vector<float>>>* capture) {
246 ++block_counter_;
247 const std::vector<std::vector<std::vector<float>>>& x =
248 render_buffer->Block(0);
249 std::vector<std::vector<std::vector<float>>>* y = capture;
250 RTC_DCHECK(render_buffer);
251 RTC_DCHECK(y);
252 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(x.size(), NumBandsForRate(sample_rate_hz_));
253 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(y->size(), NumBandsForRate(sample_rate_hz_));
254 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(x[0].size(), num_render_channels_);
255 RTC_DCHECK_EQ((*y)[0].size(), num_capture_channels_);
256 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(x[0][0].size(), kBlockSize);
257 RTC_DCHECK_EQ((*y)[0][0].size(), kBlockSize);
258
259 // Stack allocated data to use when the number of channels is low.
260 std::array<std::array<float, kFftLengthBy2>, kMaxNumChannelsOnStack> e_stack;
261 std::array<std::array<float, kFftLengthBy2Plus1>, kMaxNumChannelsOnStack>
262 Y2_stack;
263 std::array<std::array<float, kFftLengthBy2Plus1>, kMaxNumChannelsOnStack>
264 E2_stack;
265 std::array<std::array<float, kFftLengthBy2Plus1>, kMaxNumChannelsOnStack>
266 R2_stack;
267 std::array<std::array<float, kFftLengthBy2Plus1>, kMaxNumChannelsOnStack>
268 S2_linear_stack;
269 std::array<FftData, kMaxNumChannelsOnStack> Y_stack;
270 std::array<FftData, kMaxNumChannelsOnStack> E_stack;
271 std::array<FftData, kMaxNumChannelsOnStack> comfort_noise_stack;
272 std::array<FftData, kMaxNumChannelsOnStack> high_band_comfort_noise_stack;
273 std::array<SubtractorOutput, kMaxNumChannelsOnStack> subtractor_output_stack;
274
275 rtc::ArrayView<std::array<float, kFftLengthBy2>> e(e_stack.data(),
276 num_capture_channels_);
277 rtc::ArrayView<std::array<float, kFftLengthBy2Plus1>> Y2(
278 Y2_stack.data(), num_capture_channels_);
279 rtc::ArrayView<std::array<float, kFftLengthBy2Plus1>> E2(
280 E2_stack.data(), num_capture_channels_);
281 rtc::ArrayView<std::array<float, kFftLengthBy2Plus1>> R2(
282 R2_stack.data(), num_capture_channels_);
283 rtc::ArrayView<std::array<float, kFftLengthBy2Plus1>> S2_linear(
284 S2_linear_stack.data(), num_capture_channels_);
285 rtc::ArrayView<FftData> Y(Y_stack.data(), num_capture_channels_);
286 rtc::ArrayView<FftData> E(E_stack.data(), num_capture_channels_);
287 rtc::ArrayView<FftData> comfort_noise(comfort_noise_stack.data(),
288 num_capture_channels_);
289 rtc::ArrayView<FftData> high_band_comfort_noise(
290 high_band_comfort_noise_stack.data(), num_capture_channels_);
291 rtc::ArrayView<SubtractorOutput> subtractor_output(
292 subtractor_output_stack.data(), num_capture_channels_);
293 if (NumChannelsOnHeap(num_capture_channels_) > 0) {
294 // If the stack-allocated space is too small, use the heap for storing the
295 // microphone data.
296 e = rtc::ArrayView<std::array<float, kFftLengthBy2>>(e_heap_.data(),
297 num_capture_channels_);
298 Y2 = rtc::ArrayView<std::array<float, kFftLengthBy2Plus1>>(
299 Y2_heap_.data(), num_capture_channels_);
300 E2 = rtc::ArrayView<std::array<float, kFftLengthBy2Plus1>>(
301 E2_heap_.data(), num_capture_channels_);
302 R2 = rtc::ArrayView<std::array<float, kFftLengthBy2Plus1>>(
303 R2_heap_.data(), num_capture_channels_);
304 S2_linear = rtc::ArrayView<std::array<float, kFftLengthBy2Plus1>>(
305 S2_linear_heap_.data(), num_capture_channels_);
306 Y = rtc::ArrayView<FftData>(Y_heap_.data(), num_capture_channels_);
307 E = rtc::ArrayView<FftData>(E_heap_.data(), num_capture_channels_);
308 comfort_noise = rtc::ArrayView<FftData>(comfort_noise_heap_.data(),
309 num_capture_channels_);
310 high_band_comfort_noise = rtc::ArrayView<FftData>(
311 high_band_comfort_noise_heap_.data(), num_capture_channels_);
312 subtractor_output = rtc::ArrayView<SubtractorOutput>(
313 subtractor_output_heap_.data(), num_capture_channels_);
314 }
315
316 data_dumper_->DumpWav("aec3_echo_remover_capture_input", kBlockSize,
317 &(*y)[0][0][0], 16000, 1);
318 data_dumper_->DumpWav("aec3_echo_remover_render_input", kBlockSize,
319 &x[0][0][0], 16000, 1);
320 data_dumper_->DumpRaw("aec3_echo_remover_capture_input", (*y)[0][0]);
321 data_dumper_->DumpRaw("aec3_echo_remover_render_input", x[0][0]);
322
323 aec_state_.UpdateCaptureSaturation(capture_signal_saturation);
324
325 if (echo_path_variability.AudioPathChanged()) {
326 // Ensure that the gain change is only acted on once per frame.
327 if (echo_path_variability.gain_change) {
328 if (gain_change_hangover_ == 0) {
329 constexpr int kMaxBlocksPerFrame = 3;
330 gain_change_hangover_ = kMaxBlocksPerFrame;
331 rtc::LoggingSeverity log_level =
332 config_.delay.log_warning_on_delay_changes ? rtc::LS_WARNING
333 : rtc::LS_VERBOSE;
334 RTC_LOG_V(log_level)
335 << "Gain change detected at block " << block_counter_;
336 } else {
337 echo_path_variability.gain_change = false;
338 }
339 }
340
341 subtractor_.HandleEchoPathChange(echo_path_variability);
342 aec_state_.HandleEchoPathChange(echo_path_variability);
343
344 if (echo_path_variability.delay_change !=
345 EchoPathVariability::DelayAdjustment::kNone) {
346 suppression_gain_.SetInitialState(true);
347 }
348 }
349 if (gain_change_hangover_ > 0) {
350 --gain_change_hangover_;
351 }
352
353 // Analyze the render signal.
354 render_signal_analyzer_.Update(*render_buffer,
355 aec_state_.MinDirectPathFilterDelay());
356
357 // State transition.
358 if (aec_state_.TransitionTriggered()) {
359 subtractor_.ExitInitialState();
360 suppression_gain_.SetInitialState(false);
361 }
362
363 // Perform linear echo cancellation.
364 subtractor_.Process(*render_buffer, (*y)[0], render_signal_analyzer_,
365 aec_state_, subtractor_output);
366
367 // Compute spectra.
368 for (size_t ch = 0; ch < num_capture_channels_; ++ch) {
369 FormLinearFilterOutput(subtractor_output[ch], e[ch]);
370 WindowedPaddedFft(fft_, (*y)[0][ch], y_old_[ch], &Y[ch]);
371 WindowedPaddedFft(fft_, e[ch], e_old_[ch], &E[ch]);
372 LinearEchoPower(E[ch], Y[ch], &S2_linear[ch]);
373 Y[ch].Spectrum(optimization_, Y2[ch]);
374 E[ch].Spectrum(optimization_, E2[ch]);
375 }
376
377 // Optionally return the linear filter output.
378 if (linear_output) {
379 RTC_DCHECK_GE(1, linear_output->size());
380 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(num_capture_channels_, linear_output[0].size());
381 for (size_t ch = 0; ch < num_capture_channels_; ++ch) {
382 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(kBlockSize, (*linear_output)[0][ch].size());
383 std::copy(e[ch].begin(), e[ch].end(), (*linear_output)[0][ch].begin());
384 }
385 }
386
387 // Update the AEC state information.
388 aec_state_.Update(external_delay, subtractor_.FilterFrequencyResponses(),
389 subtractor_.FilterImpulseResponses(), *render_buffer, E2,
390 Y2, subtractor_output);
391
392 // Choose the linear output.
393 const auto& Y_fft = aec_state_.UseLinearFilterOutput() ? E : Y;
394
395 data_dumper_->DumpWav("aec3_output_linear", kBlockSize, &(*y)[0][0][0], 16000,
396 1);
397 data_dumper_->DumpWav("aec3_output_linear2", kBlockSize, &e[0][0], 16000, 1);
398
399 // Estimate the comfort noise.
400 cng_.Compute(aec_state_.SaturatedCapture(), Y2, comfort_noise,
401 high_band_comfort_noise);
402
403 // Only do the below processing if the output of the audio processing module
404 // is used.
405 std::array<float, kFftLengthBy2Plus1> G;
406 if (capture_output_used_) {
407 // Estimate the residual echo power.
408 residual_echo_estimator_.Estimate(aec_state_, *render_buffer, S2_linear, Y2,
409 suppression_gain_.IsDominantNearend(),
410 R2);
411
412 // Suppressor nearend estimate.
413 if (aec_state_.UsableLinearEstimate()) {
414 // E2 is bound by Y2.
415 for (size_t ch = 0; ch < num_capture_channels_; ++ch) {
416 std::transform(E2[ch].begin(), E2[ch].end(), Y2[ch].begin(),
417 E2[ch].begin(),
418 [](float a, float b) { return std::min(a, b); });
419 }
420 }
421 const auto& nearend_spectrum = aec_state_.UsableLinearEstimate() ? E2 : Y2;
422
423 // Suppressor echo estimate.
424 const auto& echo_spectrum =
425 aec_state_.UsableLinearEstimate() ? S2_linear : R2;
426
427 // Determine if the suppressor should assume clock drift.
428 const bool clock_drift = config_.echo_removal_control.has_clock_drift ||
429 echo_path_variability.clock_drift;
430
431 // Compute preferred gains.
432 float high_bands_gain;
433 suppression_gain_.GetGain(nearend_spectrum, echo_spectrum, R2,
434 cng_.NoiseSpectrum(), render_signal_analyzer_,
435 aec_state_, x, clock_drift, &high_bands_gain, &G);
436
437 suppression_filter_.ApplyGain(comfort_noise, high_band_comfort_noise, G,
438 high_bands_gain, Y_fft, y);
439
440 } else {
441 G.fill(0.f);
442 }
443
444 // Update the metrics.
445 metrics_.Update(aec_state_, cng_.NoiseSpectrum()[0], G);
446
447 // Debug outputs for the purpose of development and analysis.
448 data_dumper_->DumpWav("aec3_echo_estimate", kBlockSize,
449 &subtractor_output[0].s_refined[0], 16000, 1);
450 data_dumper_->DumpRaw("aec3_output", (*y)[0][0]);
451 data_dumper_->DumpRaw("aec3_narrow_render",
452 render_signal_analyzer_.NarrowPeakBand() ? 1 : 0);
453 data_dumper_->DumpRaw("aec3_N2", cng_.NoiseSpectrum()[0]);
454 data_dumper_->DumpRaw("aec3_suppressor_gain", G);
455 data_dumper_->DumpWav("aec3_output",
456 rtc::ArrayView<const float>(&(*y)[0][0][0], kBlockSize),
457 16000, 1);
458 data_dumper_->DumpRaw("aec3_using_subtractor_output[0]",
459 aec_state_.UseLinearFilterOutput() ? 1 : 0);
460 data_dumper_->DumpRaw("aec3_E2", E2[0]);
461 data_dumper_->DumpRaw("aec3_S2_linear", S2_linear[0]);
462 data_dumper_->DumpRaw("aec3_Y2", Y2[0]);
463 data_dumper_->DumpRaw(
464 "aec3_X2", render_buffer->Spectrum(
465 aec_state_.MinDirectPathFilterDelay())[/*channel=*/0]);
466 data_dumper_->DumpRaw("aec3_R2", R2[0]);
467 data_dumper_->DumpRaw("aec3_filter_delay",
468 aec_state_.MinDirectPathFilterDelay());
469 data_dumper_->DumpRaw("aec3_capture_saturation",
470 aec_state_.SaturatedCapture() ? 1 : 0);
471}
472
473void EchoRemoverImpl::FormLinearFilterOutput(
474 const SubtractorOutput& subtractor_output,
475 rtc::ArrayView<float> output) {
476 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(subtractor_output.e_refined.size(), output.size());
477 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(subtractor_output.e_coarse.size(), output.size());
478 bool use_refined_output = true;
479 if (use_coarse_filter_output_) {
480 // As the output of the refined adaptive filter generally should be better
481 // than the coarse filter output, add a margin and threshold for when
482 // choosing the coarse filter output.
483 if (subtractor_output.e2_coarse < 0.9f * subtractor_output.e2_refined &&
484 subtractor_output.y2 > 30.f * 30.f * kBlockSize &&
485 (subtractor_output.s2_refined > 60.f * 60.f * kBlockSize ||
486 subtractor_output.s2_coarse > 60.f * 60.f * kBlockSize)) {
487 use_refined_output = false;
488 } else {
489 // If the refined filter is diverged, choose the filter output that has
490 // the lowest power.
491 if (subtractor_output.e2_coarse < subtractor_output.e2_refined &&
492 subtractor_output.y2 < subtractor_output.e2_refined) {
493 use_refined_output = false;
494 }
495 }
496 }
497
498 SignalTransition(refined_filter_output_last_selected_
499 ? subtractor_output.e_refined
500 : subtractor_output.e_coarse,
501 use_refined_output ? subtractor_output.e_refined
502 : subtractor_output.e_coarse,
503 output);
504 refined_filter_output_last_selected_ = use_refined_output;
505}

509EchoRemover* EchoRemover::Create(const EchoCanceller3Config& config,
510 int sample_rate_hz,
511 size_t num_render_channels,
512 size_t num_capture_channels) {
513 return new EchoRemoverImpl(config, sample_rate_hz, num_render_channels,
514 num_capture_channels);
515}
